race.comment: VICTORY TUNE (8) resumes and brings strong form from metro Open 2s. He will be naturally improved, and his jumpouts have been good. Looks well-placed to break through. KINDAKANDY (7) debuts and has had a string of promising jumpouts. The in-form Brown has been aboard on most of them and rides today. That's a push and a bold run is on the cards. VALOROUS STAR (2) raced as a firm favourite at Yarra Valley on debut and may have had excuses. He'd won a Kilmore jumpout prior and is back after 19 days. A much better effort is likely. COLD LOGIC (5) debuts with the blinkers on and has had a string of jumpouts. Won the most recent and he's worth keeping onside.
